The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Truck crushes 7 in escape attempt
                                                                                                               Truck crushes 7 in escape attempt
                            
	Varanasi, July 29 (PTI): A truck that collided with an auto crushed to death seven persons who tried to block it while the driver attempted to escape at a market area in Uttar Pradeshs Mau district today.         
	Five died on the spot while two succumbed to injuries at the district hospital, Azamgarh inspector-general of police K.K. Tripathi said. Over a dozen were injured.         
	A mob burnt police posts and threw stones at Dakshin Tola police station after the accident.         
	Eyewitnesses said the cops fired several rounds in the air to disperse the crowd but the situation was still tense. One person was injured in the firing.         
	Brij Lal, the additional director-general of police, said several policemen were injured in the clashes. Lal said the police fired in the air in self-defence, adding that the situation was still out of control.         
	People indulged in heavy stone pelting, setting several vehicles  including police motorcycles  ablaze in the Dakshin Tola police station, which was the worst affected, Lal said        
	Tripathi, along with top police and administrative officials, have reached the spot. Police force has been deployed in the district.                                                                                                                                                                           
